TITLE: Introduction to Atomic Theory 01: From Alchemists to Bohr
	- Pre-requisitives: Fisica 03.
	- Co-requisitives: Quantum Mechanics 00.
	- Recommended: Classical Mechanics 02.


The atom of the Alchemists and Chemists
	- The greeks! Escolas atomicas.
	- Leis macroscopicas estelecidas (18th century)
		- Lavosier Law: Conservação da massa em reação quimica
		- Proust Law: Proporções definidas elemento-massa
	- Modelo Atômico de dalton (18th century) (published 1808~1810)
		- Explicação microscopica atômica das duas leis: Modelo de Dalton
			- Átomo maciço indivisivel
			- Elementos quimicos são átomos.
		- Elementos quimicos (different atoms)
			- Hydrogen
			- Oxygen
			- Table of them. Atom draw.
		- Example: Tin Oxide
			- Tin Oxide I and Tin Oxide II.
			- Explanation of those two laws
			- Explanation using dalton theory.
	- Refinando o Modelo de Dalton (1811)
		- Avogadro laws.
		- Natureza diatomica de vários "elementos" quimicos
		- Water is H2O (avogadro), not HO (dalton).
		- Redefinition of elements: atom
	- TODO: Avogadro experiments and the mol
	- Contribuições quantitativas de Avogadro
		- The mol
		- Def: Massa molar atômica
		- Calc: Massa aproximada de um único átomo. (ordem de grandeza)
		- Calc: Raio aproximado de um átomo (ordem de grandeza)
		- Calc: Volume aproximado de um átomo (ordem de grandeza)
		- Note: We now have: Massa e tamanho de um átomo. =).
	- What a beautiful world..... Until Thomsom descobre o eletron.......



Atomic Emission Spectrum (1880~1890)
	- Spectroscopy of chemical elements.
	- Experimental apparatus
		- Electrical discharge passes thru gas chamber (gas in question)
		- Atoms are excited, and de-excite by producing electromagnetic radiation
		- EM emission is colimated by slit
		- Colimated EM emission passes thru prism (or difracting grating)
		- Then: Light goes to photographic plate (as a line (because of the slit))
	- Emission lines
		- Show: Emission line of Helium atom.
		- Show: Emission line of Oxygen atom.
		- Show: Emission line of Nitrogen atom.
		- Note: Discrete emissions of energy
		- Note: Very contrasting with continuous emission of heated blackbody surface
		- Note: Every element has its emission lines (like a fingerprint!)
	- Balmer experiments: The Hydrogen atom
		- Show: Emission line of Hydrogen atom
		- Data: Emission lines of the hydrogen atom
		- Sequence of converging lines
		- The value of the convergence: 3645.6A.
		- Balmer series
		- Balmer Formula (1885)
	- Hydrogen series. Math sequences of lines.
		- Lyman Series: Ultraviolet.
		- Balmer: Visible and near ultraviolet
		- Etc..
		- Def: Rydberg constant.
		- Experimental value: R = 10967757.6 pm 1.2 1/meter.
		- Note: Rydberg constant percentage of error due to measurement.
		- Note: Pretty precise, isn't it?
	- Família dos metais alcalinos
		- Emissão consistente e previsivel
		- Sequencias de linhas
		- Rydberg constant for each element
		- Constants for a series
	- Observations of Rydberg constant
		- Almost the same for all elements
		- Slight increase proportional to atomic weight



